  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An automation engineer needs to push a configuration change to a single Cisco IOS-XE router using an HTTP-based interface that leverages YANG models and supports both JSON and XML encoding. Which protocol should the engineer use?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"NETCONF"},{"id":"b","text":"gNMI"},{"id":"c","text":"RESTCONF"},{"id":"d","text":"SNMP"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material describes RESTCONF (RFC 8040) as an 'HTTP(S) wrapper around NETCONF/YANG with JSON/XML,' making it the correct choice for an HTTP-based, YANG-backed protocol that supports both JSON and XML. NETCONF uses SSH (not HTTP). gNMI uses gRPC for model-driven telemetry. SNMP is a legacy protocol not based on YANG models or HTTP.$patch$, $patch$Automation and Programmability$patch$,
