INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A network operations team wants to automate configuration changes across 50 Cisco routers without installing any software agent on the devices. Which configuration management tool best fits this requirement?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Puppet"},{"id":"b","text":"Chef"},{"id":"c","text":"Ansible"},{"id":"d","text":"Terraform"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material explicitly states 'Ansible: agentless, YAML playbooks, modules (ios_config, ios_facts).' Because Ansible is agentless, it requires no software to be installed on the managed devices, making it ideal for network automation at scale. Puppet and Chef are described as 'agent-based,' meaning they require a software agent on each node. Terraform is a declarative infrastructure-as-code tool focused on provisioning, not ongoing configuration management of existing network OS devices.$patch$, $patch$Automation and Programmability$patch$,
