INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An administrator is configuring an IP phone on a Cisco switch port. The switch needs to send voice traffic on VLAN 100 while data traffic from a PC attached to the phone travels on VLAN 10. Which feature enables the switch to inform the IP phone of the correct voice VLAN?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"VTP (VLAN Trunking Protocol)"},{"id":"b","text":"CDP (Cisco Discovery Protocol) or LLDP-MED"},{"id":"c","text":"DTP (Dynamic Trunking Protocol)"},{"id":"d","text":"STP (Spanning Tree Protocol)"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states: 'Voice VLAN: separate L2 for IP phones via CDP/LLDP-MED.' The switch uses CDP (on Cisco devices) or LLDP-MED (the open standard equivalent) to communicate voice VLAN information to the IP phone. The phone then tags its voice frames with VLAN 100 while the PC's data frames remain untagged on VLAN 10. VTP propagates VLAN database information between switches, not voice VLAN assignments to phones. DTP negotiates trunk modes between switches. STP provides loop prevention.$patch$, $patch$Network Access$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/switches/lan/catalyst9300/software/release/17-9/configuration_guide/vlan/b_179_vlan_9300_cg/configuring_voice_vlan.html","label":"Cisco – Configuring Voice VLANs"},{"url":"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/tech/data-link-layer-switching/cisco-discovery-protocol-cdp/index.html","label":"Cisco – Cisco Discovery Protocol (CDP) Overview"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
