INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A network administrator needs to allow DHCP clients on a remote subnet (192.168.10.0/24) to obtain addresses from a DHCP server located at 10.1.1.100. The router interface facing the client subnet is Gi0/1. Which command must be applied to interface Gi0/1 to relay DHCP broadcasts to the server?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"ip helper-address 10.1.1.100"},{"id":"b","text":"ip dhcp relay 10.1.1.100"},{"id":"c","text":"ip dhcp-server 10.1.1.100"},{"id":"d","text":"ip forward-protocol udp 67 10.1.1.100"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["a"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states 'ip helper-address for relaying DHCP across subnets.' When a router receives a DHCP broadcast on an interface, the ip helper-address command unicasts that request to the specified DHCP server IP. Option B ('ip dhcp relay') is not a valid IOS command. Option C ('ip dhcp-server') does not exist. Option D references ip forward-protocol, which is a related but separate mechanism; the correct and standard command is ip helper-address applied to the client-facing interface.$patch$, $patch$IP Services$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/ios-xml/ios/ipaddr_dhcp/configuration/xe-16/dhcp-xe-16-book/config-dhcp-relay-agent.html","label":"Cisco - Configuring the Cisco IOS DHCP Relay Agent"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
