INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$Which southbound protocol does Cisco DNA Center (Catalyst Center) use to communicate with and program managed network devices?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"REST over HTTPS on port 443"},{"id":"b","text":"SNMP v2c traps"},{"id":"c","text":"NETCONF/YANG"},{"id":"d","text":"Telnet over port 23"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states: 'Southbound NETCONF/YANG to devices' when describing Cisco DNA Center. NETCONF combined with YANG data models is how DNA Center programs the data plane on managed devices. REST over HTTPS is used for DNA Center's Northbound API (consumed by external automation scripts), not the southbound interface to devices. SNMP v2c is a legacy monitoring protocol not used for southbound programmability in DNA Center. Telnet is unencrypted and deprecated in modern network management.$patch$, $patch$Automation and Programmability$patch$,
