INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A developer calls a Cisco DNA Center REST API endpoint and receives an HTTP status code of 403. What does this response indicate?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The request was successful and the resource was created."},{"id":"b","text":"The server encountered an internal error processing the request."},{"id":"c","text":"The client is authenticated but does not have permission to access the requested resource."},{"id":"d","text":"The client has not provided valid authentication credentials."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material lists 403 Forbidden as a 4xx client error meaning the client lacks permission to access the resource, even if authenticated. This differs from 401 Unauthorized, which indicates that valid authentication credentials were not provided at all. A 201 status indicates successful resource creation (2xx), and 500 is a server-side error (5xx). Understanding the distinction between 401 and 403 is critical when troubleshooting Cisco DNA Center API calls.$patch$, $patch$Automation and Programmability$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://developer.cisco.com/docs/dna-center/api/2-3-7/","label":"Cisco DNA Center API Reference – Authentication and Authorization"},{"url":"https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Status/403","label":"MDN Web Docs – HTTP Response Status Codes"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
