         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"GET"},{"id":"b","text":"DELETE"},{"id":"c","text":"POST"},{"id":"d","text":"PATCH"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["c"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states that POST is the HTTP method used to create a new resource in a REST API. GET is used to read data, DELETE removes a resource, and PATCH modifies an existing resource partially. Since the VLAN does not yet exist, POST is the correct choice.$patch$, $patch$Automation and Programmability$patch$,
