INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A developer sends an HTTP POST request to the Cisco DNA Center northbound REST API to create a new network site. The server responds with status code 201. What does this status code indicate?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"The request was received but is still being processed."},{"id":"b","text":"The resource was successfully created."},{"id":"c","text":"The request was unauthorized and authentication is required."},{"id":"d","text":"The server encountered an internal error."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material lists HTTP status codes: '2xx (success: 200 OK, 201 Created, 204 No Content).' A 201 Created response confirms the server successfully created the requested resource. A 401 would indicate authentication is required. A 500 would indicate a server-side error. There is no standard 'still processing' semantic for 201.$patch$, $patch$Automation and Programmability$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://developer.cisco.com/docs/dna-center/","label":"Cisco DNA Center API Documentation"},{"url":"https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc9110#section-15.3.2","label":"RFC 9110 – HTTP Semantics: Status Codes"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = '200-301-P6'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A developer sends an HTTP POST request to the Cisco DNA Center northbound REST API to create a new network site. The server responds with status code 201. What does this status code indicate?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$Which of the following best describes the architectural difference between a traditional network and a Software-Defined Network (SDN)?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Traditional networks use a centralized control plane, while SDN distributes the control plane to each device."},{"id":"b","text":"Traditional networks have a distributed control plane on each device, while SDN centralizes the control plane in a controller."},{"id":"c","text":"SDN eliminates the data plane entirely and processes all traffic in the controller."},{"id":"d","text":"Traditional networks rely on REST APIs, while SDN uses CLI-only management."}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states: 'Traditional: distributed control plane (each device runs routing). SDN: centralized control plane (controller programs data plane).' In SDN, the controller makes forwarding decisions and programs the data plane of individual devices; the data plane itself is not eliminated. Traditional networks use distributed routing protocols, not REST APIs, as their primary management paradigm.$patch$, $patch$Automation and Programmability$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/solutions/software-defined-networking/overview.html","label":"Cisco Software-Defined Networking Overview"},{"url":"https://www.ciscopress.com/store/ccna-200-301-official-cert-guide-library-9781587147142","label":"Cisco CCNA 200-301 Official Cert Guide – SDN Chapter"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = '200-301-P6'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$Which of the following best describes the architectural difference between a traditional network and a Software-Defined Network (SDN)?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A network programmer needs a Python library to connect to multiple vendor devices over SSH and execute show commands without using a vendor-specific SDK. Which Python library, cited in the CCNA automation domain, is specifically designed as an SSH client abstraction for network devices?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"requests"},{"id":"b","text":"Netmiko"},{"id":"c","text":"Nornir"},{"id":"d","text":"Terraform"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material identifies: 'Netmiko: SSH library for network devices.' Netmiko is purpose-built to simplify SSH connections to network devices. 'requests' is an HTTP client library for REST API calls. Nornir is an orchestration framework (not just an SSH library). Terraform is an infrastructure-as-code tool, not a Python SSH library.$patch$, $patch$Automation and Programmability$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://github.com/ktbyers/netmiko","label":"Netmiko GitHub Repository"},{"url":"https://developer.cisco.com/learning/tracks/netprog-eng/","label":"Cisco DevNet – Network Programmability Basics"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = '200-301-P6'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A network programmer needs a Python library to connect to multiple vendor devices over SSH and execute show commands without using a vendor-specific SDK. Which Python library, cited in the CCNA automation domain, is specifically designed as an SSH client abstraction for network devices?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$An engineer needs to modify a single attribute on an existing REST API resource without replacing the entire object. Which HTTP method should be used?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"GET"},{"id":"b","text":"POST"},{"id":"c","text":"PUT"},{"id":"d","text":"PATCH"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["d"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material defines HTTP methods as: 'GET (read), POST (create), PUT (replace), PATCH (modify), DELETE (remove).' PATCH is used to partially modify an existing resource, making it the correct choice when only one attribute needs to change. PUT replaces the entire resource. POST creates a new resource. GET only retrieves data.$patch$, $patch$Automation and Programmability$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.rfc-editor.org/rfc/rfc5789","label":"RFC 5789 – PATCH Method for HTTP"},{"url":"https://developer.cisco.com/learning/modules/rest-api-fundamentals/","label":"Cisco DevNet – REST API Fundamentals"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = '200-301-P6'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$An engineer needs to modify a single attribute on an existing REST API resource without replacing the entire object. Which HTTP method should be used?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$Which Cisco on-device automation feature allows a network engineer to trigger a configuration change or script automatically when a specific syslog event is detected on an IOS device, without any external controller?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Cisco DNA Center Assurance"},{"id":"b","text":"Cisco Embedded Event Manager (EEM)"},{"id":"c","text":"Ansible ios_config module"},{"id":"d","text":"RESTCONF with YANG models"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material states: 'Cisco EEM (Embedded Event Manager): on-device automation via applets and Tcl scripts.' EEM runs directly on the IOS device and can react to events such as syslog messages, CLI input, or interface state changes without any external controller. DNA Center Assurance is a monitoring feature. Ansible ios_config requires an external control node. RESTCONF is a programmability interface, not an event-driven on-device automation tool.$patch$, $patch$Automation and Programmability$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/ios-xml/ios/eem/configuration/xe-16/eem-xe-16-book.html","label":"Cisco IOS Embedded Event Manager (EEM) Configuration Guide"},{"url":"https://developer.cisco.com/docs/ios-xe/#!embedded-event-manager","label":"Cisco DevNet – EEM Overview"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = '200-301-P6'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$Which Cisco on-device automation feature allows a network engineer to trigger a configuration change or script automatically when a specific syslog event is detected on an IOS device, without any external controller?$patch$);
INSERT INTO "Question" (id, "examId", stem, type, options, correct, explanation, domain, difficulty, "references", status, "generatedBy", "isTeaser", "createdAt", "updatedAt")
  SELECT gen_random_uuid()::text, e.id, $patch$A network architect is designing a solution where business intent is automatically translated into network device configurations across the entire enterprise fabric. Which Cisco platform and concept best represents this capability?$patch$, 'SINGLE'::"QType",
         $json$[{"id":"a","text":"Cisco IOS EEM applets performing Tcl-based scripting"},{"id":"b","text":"Cisco DNA Center / Catalyst Center implementing Intent-Based Networking (IBN)"},{"id":"c","text":"Ansible playbooks using YAML to configure individual routers over SSH"},{"id":"d","text":"NAPALM providing multi-vendor abstraction for CLI commands"}]$json$::jsonb, $json$["b"]$json$::jsonb, $patch$The source material describes Cisco DNA Center / Catalyst Center as providing 'Intent-based networking (IBN) - business intent translated to network config,' along with 'Assurance, automation, and analytics' via a northbound REST API and southbound NETCONF/YANG to devices. This centralized, intent-driven approach is the defining feature of DNA Center. EEM is on-device and reactive. Ansible operates at a per-device configuration level without holistic intent abstraction. NAPALM is a Python abstraction library, not an intent-based platform.$patch$, $patch$Automation and Programmability$patch$,
         3, $json$[{"url":"https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/products/cloud-systems-management/dna-center/index.html","label":"Cisco DNA Center – Intent-Based Networking"},{"url":"https://developer.cisco.com/docs/dna-center/","label":"Cisco Catalyst Center Documentation"}]$json$::jsonb, 'DRAFT'::"QStatus", 'claude-sonnet-4-6', false, NOW(), NOW()
  FROM "Exam" e WHERE e.code = '200-301-P6'
  AND NOT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM "Question" q2 WHERE q2."examId" = e.id AND q2.stem = $patch$A network architect is designing a solution where business intent is automatically translated into network device configurations across the entire enterprise fabric. Which Cisco platform and concept best represents this capability?$patch$);

